The article is a statement by the President on the 18th anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda. The President reflects on the horrific events of 1994, where 800,000 people lost their lives in 100 days. The statement emphasizes the shared responsibility of nations to protect civilians and prevent such evil from happening again. The United States expresses grief for the Rwandan people and acknowledges Rwanda's progress in moving beyond the tragedy. The US government and American people pledge to continue supporting Rwanda in its efforts to build a peaceful and prosperous future.